Diagnosis. Males are distinguished by their unique median apophysis with strong pointed projection basally (
Figs 25, 26
). Females are distinguished by the heart-shaped median sector of their epigynum (
Fig. 27
), from
C. cuchilla
by the copulatory openings positioned laterally (
Fig. 28
), rather than ventrally as in the later species (
Fig. 12
).

Distribution. Ecuador : Cotopaxi and Santo Domingo de los Tsáchilas Provinces (
Fig. 57
).
